
# lproj

This is the R package `lproj' (Local Projections) developed by Christian Brownlees (http://www.econ.upf.edu/~cbrownlees/)

# Installation

You can install the stable version from CRAN:

http://cran.r-project.org/package=lproj

or from the R prompt

> install.packages('lproj', dependencies = TRUE)

Alternatively, you can download the development version from github:

 - zip: https://github.com/ctbrownlees/R-Package-lproj/zipball/master
 - tar ball: https://github.com/ctbrownlees/R-Package-lproj/tarball/master

and install it using `R CMD INSTALL`.

You can also install the development version using the devtools package:

> library(devtools) 
> install_github('R-Package-lproj', 'ctbrownlees')

Note: Windows users have to first install Rtools (http://www.murdoch-sutherland.com/Rtools/).

